            <abstract>
                <p>A kind of eternal calendar, which calculates <foreign xml:lang="gez">ṭǝntewon</foreign>,
                    <foreign xml:lang="gez">maṭqǝʿ</foreign>, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ʾabaqte</foreign>, the beginning of the
                    fast of Niniveh and <foreign xml:lang="gez">ṣom</foreign>, the day of Jewish Pascha, the Christian Easter and Pentecost 
                    according to the weekday of the first day of the year, thematically similar to <ref type="work" corresp="LIT6957HassabaHegg"/>,
                    <ref type="work" corresp="LIT6563HassabHeg"/>, <ref type="mss" corresp="IVorlov34"/>, 
                    <ref type="mss" corresp="BNFabb96"/>, <ref type="mss" corresp="BLorient13269"/>, <ref type="mss" corresp="BLorient2082"/> 
                    and <ref type="mss" corresp="#Tanasee34">Ṭānāsee 34, ff. 100ra‒104rb</ref>). 
                    Some events from Ethiopian history are mentioned at times partly in form of later additions, 
                    e.g. <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወበዝየ፡ ሞተ፡ አቃቤ፡ ሰዓት፡ <persName ref="PRS14938Abranyos">አብራንዮስ።</persName></foreign>, 
                    who is possibly the mamhǝr of Kǝbrān, promoted to the rank of the ʾaqābe saʿāt.</p>
            </abstract>
